249
00:18:22,890 --> 00:18:24,350
catch up, talking about stuff?

250
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:26,190
Why did you lie and say you signed up for an exam academy?

251
00:18:26,190 --> 00:18:28,790
 Che Gyeong never signed up for our academy.

252
00:18:28,790 --> 00:18:30,370
 Are you sure she's preparing for the exam?

253
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:32,500
I discreetly looked into other academies as well.

254
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:35,220
I don't think she is attending any exam schools.

255
00:18:36,230 --> 00:18:37,110
About that...

256
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:39,110
You don't go to an academy. You don't pick up your phone.

257
00:18:39,110 --> 00:18:40,760
So did you get any studying done?

258
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,840
I know you didn't, so shut it.

259
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:45,400
For today, just shut up and come out with me. Then I'll forgive you.

260
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,670
What a scary way to ask me out on a date.

261
00:18:47,670 --> 00:18:49,730
Why would I go on a date with you?

262
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:52,870
- You're meeting a guy. 
 - A guy?

263
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:55,290
Cheers!

264
00:18:57,790 --> 00:18:59,920
Wow, that's good.

265
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,700
Che Gyeong, it's been way too long.

266
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:05,660
- Come to our club meetups more often.
 - Me?

267
00:19:05,660 --> 00:19:08,480
Did my doppelganger go around signing up for clubs by any chance?

268
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,760
Yeah, that's right.

269
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,960
You signed up for a dance club, manga club, and whatnot.

270
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:14,360
Oh, right. I remember.

271
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:16,610
Sunbae, you told me to just fill out the application form.

272
00:19:16,610 --> 00:19:21,150
So you could get drinks from the dance club president, like some kind of multi-level marketing scheme.

273
00:19:21,150 --> 00:19:23,100
Sunbae, it has been a while so it's good to see you.

274
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:26,620
- Introduce us to your friends!
 - Sure. Sure.

275
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:28,350
This is my friend from high school.

276
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:32,230
Kim Si Hyeok who was just appointed as the Minister of the Office for Government Policy Coordination.

277
00:19:32,230 --> 00:19:34,520
This is Jeong Ba Reum whom I met during my study abroad.

278
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:36,990
He works for RBS in the drama department.

279
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:38,870
Hello.

280
00:19:38,870 --> 00:19:40,690
Hello.

281
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,720
Che Gyeong, is there anything you want to ask him?

282
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:46,580
You used to want to get into RBS.

283
00:19:47,450 --> 00:19:48,800
- I did? 
 - Yeah.

284
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:53,050
You said you were going to get an RBS employee ID no matter what.

285
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:55,370
Did I?

286
00:19:55,370 --> 00:19:59,320
Oh, because I used to really like RBS dramas.

287
00:20:00,450 --> 00:20:02,330
But your company is a little bit of a gamble.

288
00:20:02,330 --> 00:20:04,700
There are some masterpieces, but some are just so soapy.

289
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:07,380
Don't make trash like that.

290
00:20:07,380 --> 00:20:09,850
What's trash?

291
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:13,290
I'm curious, too. Does RBS have a super soapy drama?

292
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:15,100
Recently there is "Accounting for the Married" or something.

293
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:18,780
Killing the wife for money, then killing someone else. That drama.

294
00:20:18,780 --> 00:20:21,500
How can you have trash like that on national television?

295
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:23,110
The viewers are messed up,

296
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,900
but the people who make it need to do some self-reflection, too.

297
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,860
If my future wife says she will watch something like that,

298
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:28,870
I'll divorce her right away.

299
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:31,900
How would you get a divorce?

300
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:34,660
You need to be married to get a divorce.

301
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:39,080
That's right. Che Gyeong, you're so smart.

302
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,480
You're not even married yet, but you're already talking about divorce.

303
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:43,270
- Must keep you busy. 
 - I don't think so.

304
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:44,860
You'll never tie the knot anyway.

305
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:47,650
- Hey, are you drunk? 
 - No, I'm not drunk.

306
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:50,110
I am very sober. You know why?

307
00:20:50,110 --> 00:20:52,220
Because that drama is not about that.

308
00:20:52,220 --> 00:20:55,540
It's not about killing the wife and killing others for money at all.

309
00:20:55,540 --> 00:20:59,720
Someone who can't even comprehend a drama plot is running our country with the taxes I pay.

310
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:04,020
Wow, I thought I cured my insomnia, but it seems like it will come back.

311
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,600
Hey, Go Che Gyeong!

312
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,890
What is wrong with you?

313
00:21:17,890 --> 00:21:22,020
I had something to tell you. That's why I told you we should just eat at home.

314
00:21:22,020 --> 00:21:23,680
But today really won't work.

315
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,550
I'll tell you later. Next time.

316
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:27,320
Bye.

317
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,420
 It was good at the beginning because Writer Hwang wrote it before she left.

318
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:49,400
 It feels so formulaic.

319
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,200
 It's so obvious that she cares about the viewer response too much.

320
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:55,520
 Can't they just change the writer right now?

321
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:09,020

322
00:22:09,020 --> 00:22:11,180
A perfect destiny that will be the talk of the town for a long time

323
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:13,550
is about to start.

324
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:16,270
On a perfect night like this...

325
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:19,070
we need magenta pink rain.

326
00:22:42,740 --> 00:22:45,480
 It's magenta pink rain!

327
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:10,400
Excuse me, sir. I'm getting off.

328
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:34,860
 Every human is a work of God.

329
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:45,250
♫  If I could return  ♫

330
00:23:45,250 --> 00:23:50,600
♫  Once again to that time  ♫

331
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:56,700
♫  Even if my heart aches and feels sad  ♫

332
00:23:56,700 --> 00:24:02,660
♫  It would be a good memory  ♫

333
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,990
♫  Rewind the day  ♫

334
00:24:07,990 --> 00:24:11,490
 Human beings who are born into lives written for them by gods

335
00:24:11,490 --> 00:24:14,560
 grasp concepts of happiness and sadness

336
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:17,710
 and commit acts of good and evil as they live.

337
00:24:17,710 --> 00:24:20,880
♫  I want to tell you  ♫

338
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:24,250
 Whoever feels happy will go through an equal amount of hardship.

339
00:24:24,250 --> 00:24:27,630
 Whoever suffers will gain an equal amount of wisdom.

340
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:34,010
 But regarding love...

341
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:36,960
 Love is the only thing that is unfair.

342
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:41,980
♫  Please stay with me  ♫

343
00:24:55,020 --> 00:25:02,010

344
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:11,530
♫  Standing several steps apart  ♫

345
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:15,990
♫  You and I are at this place  ♫

346
00:25:15,990 --> 00:25:18,540
♫  Two people are looking like this  ♫

347
00:25:18,540 --> 00:25:20,260
 Love.

348
00:25:20,260 --> 00:25:22,000
 Love is...

349
00:25:22,940 --> 00:25:27,170
 a gift from god for the courageous.

350
00:25:27,170 --> 00:25:32,940
♫  We desired each other  ♫

351
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:36,120

352
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:41,240
♫  If I had known  ♫

353
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:46,440
♫  The one person who could comfort my tired heart  ♫

354
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:50,710
♫  is still you  ♫

355
00:25:50,710 --> 00:25:55,270
♫  I would have been a little warmer and affectionate to you   ♫

356
00:25:55,270 --> 00:26:04,100
♫  And quickly hugged you tightly first  ♫

357
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:09,300
♫  But you went the long way around to come back here  ♫

358
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:12,610
♫  To my small crumpled heart   ♫
